    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-04-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-05-06T16:11:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>BPA-Free Kids Act of 2008 - Treats as a banned hazardous substance under the Federal Hazardous Substances Act any consumer product that contains a detectable amount of bisphenol A (commonly known as BPA) and that is designed for or intended for use by, or care of, a child seven years of age or younger. Permits state laws that provide equal or greater protection.</p> <p>Requires a study on the health effects of BPA exposure in all age groups and in pregnant women.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
